grey|NH}} || {{grey|NH}} || {{grey|NH}} || || 10,152 || [[Helong Sports Center Stadium|Helong Stadium]]\n|-\n| [[2011 China League One|2011]] || bgcolor=#FFFFE0|2 || 26 || 13 || 8 || 5 || 36 || 27 || 9 || 47 || bgcolor=silver|RU || R2 || {{grey|NH}} || {{grey|NH}} || || || Dongguan Nancheng Stadium <br> [[Yuexiushan Stadium]]\n|-\n| [[2012 Chinese Super League|2012]] || bgcolor=#D0F0C0|1 || 30 || 13 || 3 || 14 || 47 || 49 || \u22122 || 42 || 7 || R4 || DNQ || {{grey|NH}} || || 8,460 || [[Yuexiushan Stadium]] <br> [[Guangzhou Higher Education Mega Center Central Stadium|Guangzhou HEMC Central Stadium]]\n|-\n| [[2013 Chinese Super League|2013]] || bgcolor=#D0F0C0|1 || 30 || 11 || 7 || 12 || 45 || 47 || \u22122 || 40 || 6 || R4 || DNQ || {{grey|NH}} || || 10,384 || [[Yuexiushan Stadium]]\n|-\n| [[2014 Chinese Super League|2014]] || bgcolor=#D0F0C0|1 || 30 || 17 || 6 || 7  || 67 || 39 || 28 || 57 || bgcolor=#FFA500|3 || R4 || DNQ || {{grey|NH}} || || 11,487 || [[Yuexiushan Stadium]]\n|-\n| [[2015 Chinese Super League|2015]] || bgcolor=#D0F0C0|1 || 30 || 8 || 7 || 15 || 35 || 41 || \u22126 || 31 || 14 || R4 || DNQ || {{grey|NH}} || [[2015 AFC Champions League|Group]] || 7,989 || [[Yuexiushan Stadium]] <br> [[Guangzhou Higher Education Mega Center Central Stadium|Guangzhou HEMC Central Stadium]]\n|-\n| [[2016 Chinese Super League|2016]] || bgcolor=#D0F0C0|1 || 30 || 11 || 7 || 12 || 47 || 50 || \u22123 || 40 || 6 || SF || DNQ || {{grey|NH}} ||  || 9,831 || [[Yuexiushan Stadium]]\n|-\n| [[2017 Chinese Super League|2017]] || bgcolor=#D0F0C0|1 || 30 ||15||7||8||59||46||13||52||5|| QF || DNQ || {{grey|NH}} ||  ||9,904|| [[Yuexiushan Stadium]] <br> [[Guangdong Provincial People's Stadium]]\n|-\n| [[2018 Chinese Super League|2018]] || bgcolor=#D0F0C0|1 || 30 || 10 || 6 || 14 || 49 || 61 || \u221212 || 36 || 10 || SF || DNQ || {{grey|NH}} ||  || 10,321 || [[Yuexiushan Stadium]]\n|-\n| [[2019 Chinese Super League|2019]] || bgcolor=#D0F0C0|1 || 30 ||9\n|5\n|16\n|54\n|72\n|<nowiki>-18</nowiki>\n|32\n|12\n| R4 || DNQ || {{grey|NH}} ||  ||  || [[Yuexiushan Stadium]]\n|}\n*{{note|1|1}} in group stage\n*{{note|2|2}} Liaoning B team promoted to 1 level, but according to CFA rules a club could only enter 1 team in top level so that Senyang replaced Liaoning B's place in 1 level\n*{{note|3|3}} Joins 1994 Jia-A League as 1992 member\n*{{note|4|4}} no relegation\n\nKey\n<div>\n{{col-begin-small}}\n{{col-4}}\n{| style=\"border: 1px solid #ffffff; background-color: #ffffff\" cellspacing=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\"\n|-\n| bgcolor=\"#D0F0C0\" width=\"20\" | \n| bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" align=\"left\" |&nbsp;&nbsp;[[Chinese Super League|China top division]]\n|-\n| bgcolor=\"#FFFFE0\" width=\"20\" | \n| bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" align=\"left\" |&nbsp;&nbsp;[[China League One|China second division]]\n|-\n! bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" width=\"20\" | \n| bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" align=\"left\" |&nbsp;&nbsp;[[China League Two|China third division]]\n|-\n! bgcolor=\"#FFD700\" width=\"20\" | W\n| bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" align=\"left\" |&nbsp;&nbsp;Winners\n|-\n! bgcolor=\"#C0C0C0\" width=\"20\" | RU\n| bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" align=\"left\" |&nbsp;&nbsp;Runners-up\n|-\n! bgcolor=\"#FFA500\" width=\"20\" | 3\n| bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" align=\"left\" |&nbsp;&nbsp;Third place\n|-\n! bgcolor=\"#ffcccc\" width=\"20\" | \n| bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" align=\"left\" |&nbsp;&nbsp;Relegated\n|}\n</div>\n{{col-4}}\n* Pld = Played\n* W = Games won\n* D = Games drawn\n* L = Games lost\n* F = Goals for\n* A = Goals against\n* Pts = Points\n* Pos = Final position\n{{col-4}}\n* DNQ = Did not qualify\n* DNE = Did not enter\n* NH = Not Held\n*&nbsp;\u2013 = Does Not Exist\n* R1 = Round 1\n* R2 = Round 2\n* R3 = Round 3\n* R4 = Round 4\n{{col-4}}\n* F = Final\n* SF = Semi-finals\n* QF = Quarter-finals\n* R16 = Round of 16\n* Group = Group stage\n* GS2 = Second Group stage\n* QR1 = First Qualifying Round\n* QR2 = Second Qualifying Round\n* QR3 = Third Qualifying Round\n{{col-end}}\n\n=== International results ===\n{{main|Guangzhou R&F F.C. in Asian football}}Guangzhou R&F played in the Asian Champions League in 2015. They beat Singaporean side [[Warriors FC]] and Australian team [[Central Coast Mariners FC|Central Coast Mariners]] in the qualifying rounds but were knocked-out in the group stage.\n\n== R&F (Hong Kong) ==\n{{main|R&F (Hong Kong)}}\nIn August 2016 it was announced that R&F had entered a satellite team into the [[Hong Kong Premier League]]. Players registered for the Chinese Super League are ineligible to play in the Hong Kong Premier League, and vice versa.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gzrffc.com.cn/index.php?m=Article&a=show&id=1511|title=\u6e2f\u8d85\u6211\u4eec\u6765\u5566\uff01\u6559\u5e08\u8282\u5c06\u8fce\u9996\u79c0-\u8d5b\u4e8b\u65b0\u95fb|website=www.gzrffc.com.cn|access-date=2016-08-27|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180315003724/http://www.gzrffc.com.cn/index.php?m=Article&a=show&id=1511|archivedate=2018-03-15}}</ref> [[R&F (Hong Kong)]] played their home matches at the [[Siu Sai Wan Sports Ground]] during the first season. The following year, they were permitted to play their home matches at [[Yanzigang Stadium]] in Guangzhou under the condition that all away teams' travelling expenses would be covered by R&F.<ref>{{cite web|title=R&F\u5bcc\u529b\u64ec\u4e3b\u5834\u8cfd\u4e8b\u5167\u5730\u4e0a\u6f14 \u6e2f\u8d85\u7403\u6703\u63d0\u51fa\u7b54\u5141\u689d\u4ef6|url=https://www.upower.com.hk/article/67566-rf%E5%AF%8C%E5%8A%9B%E6%93%AC%E4%B8%BB%E5%A0%B4%E8%B3%BD%E4%BA%8B%E5%85%A7%E5%9C%B0%E4%B8%8A%E6%BC%94-%E6%B8%AF%E8%B6%85%E7%90%83%E6%9C%83%E6%8F%90%E5%87%BA%E7%AD%94%E5%85%81%E6%A2%9D%E4%BB%B6|website=Upower|accessdate=16 June 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180315200014/https://www.upower.com.hk/article/67566-rf%e5%af%8c%e5%8a%9b%e6%93%ac%e4%b8%bb%e5%a0%b4%e8%b3%bd%e4%ba%8b%e5%85%a7%e5%9c%b0%e4%b8%8a%e6%bc%94-%e6%b8%af%e8%b6%85%e7%90%83%e6%9c%83%e6%8f%90%e5%87%ba%e7%ad%94%e5%85%81%e6%a2%9d%e4%bb%b6|archivedate=15 March 2018}} {{in lang|zh-hk}}</ref>\n\n== Past and present internationals ==\n<small>This list contains the present and former international football players playing for Guangzhou R&F.</small><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.national-football-teams.com/club/13942/2018_2/Guangzhou_R_F.html|title=Guangzhou R&F |publisher=national-football-teams.com}}</ref>\n\n{{col-begin-small}}\n{{col-2}}\n;{{fb|Australia}}\n*[[Apostolos Giannou]] (2016\u20132017)\n<br>\n;{{fb|China}}\n*[[Jiang Ning]] (2013\u20132015)\n*[[Jiang Zhipeng]] (2014\u20132017)\n*[[Tang Miao (footballer, born October 1990)|Tang Miao]] (2011\u2013present)\n*[[Xiao Zhi]] (2016\u2013present)\n*[[Xu Bo]] (2004\u20132014)\n*[[Yu Yang (footballer)|Yu Yang]] (2015\u20132016)\n*[[Zhang Yuan (footballer, born 1989)|Zhang Yuan]] (2012\u20132015)\n<br>\n;{{fb|DR Congo}}\n*[[Jeremy Bokila]] (2015)\n<br>\n;{{fb|Israel}}\n*[[Eran Zahavi]] (2016\u2013present)\n*[[Dia Saba]] (2019\u2013present) \n<br>\n{{col-2}}\n;{{fb|Hong Kong}}\n*[[Tan Chun Lok]] (2019\u2013present)\n<br>\n;{{fb|South Korea}}\n*[[Jang Hyun-soo]] (2014\u20132017)\n*[[Park Jong-woo]] (2014\u20132015)\n<br>\n;{{fb|Morocco}}\n*[[Abderrazak Hamdallah]] (2014\u20132015)\n<br>\n;{{fb|Nigeria}}\n*[[Yakubu (footballer)|Yakubu Ayegbeni]] (2012-2013)\n*[[Aaron Samuel Olanare]] (2014\u20132015)\n<br>\n;{{fb|Sweden}}\n*[[Gustav Svensson]] (2016)\n{{col-end}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.gzrffc.com.cn Official Site] {{in lang|zh}}\n* [http://cache.images.globalsportsmedia.com/soccer/teams/150x150/425.png Guangzhou R&F logo]\n* [http://www.weltfussballarchiv.com/club_profile.php?ID=3161 Weltfussballarchiv]\n\n{{Guangzhou R&F F.C.}}\n{{Chinese Super League}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Guangzhou R and F F.C.}}\n[[Category:Guangzhou R&F F.C.| ]]\n[[Category:Football clubs in China]]\n[[Category:Football clubs in Guangdong]]\n[[Category:Football clubs in Guangzhou]]\n[[Category:Association football clubs established in 1986]]\n[[Category:1986 establishments in China]]\n", "name_user": "Kuanzhu", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guangzhou_R%26F_F.C."}
