{"title_page": "2016 Big Ten Men's Lacrosse Tournament", "text_new": "{{Infobox tournament\n| name = [[Big Ten Conference Men's Lacrosse Tournament|Big Ten Conference<br/>Men's Lacrosse Tournament]]\n| sport = [[College lacrosse#NCAA Men's Lacrosse|College lacrosse]]\n| year = 2016\n| image =\n| caption = \n| location = Baltimore, Maryland\n| established = 2015\n| administrator =\n| tournament_format = Single elimination\n| host = Johns Hopkins University\n| venues = Homewood Field \n| teams = 4\n| champion = [[Maryland Terrapins men's lacrosse|Maryland]]\n| runner-up1 = [[Rutgers Scarlet Knights men's lacrosse|Rutgers]]\n| attendance = \n| mvp = \n| top_scorer = \n| top_try_scorer = \n| website = [http://www.hopkinssports.com/sports/m-lacros/2016-big10-tournament.html HopkinsSports.com]\n| previous = [[2015 Big Ten Conference Men's Lacrosse Tournament|2015]]\n| next = [[2017 Big Ten Conference Men's Lacrosse Tournament|2017]]\n}}\nThe '''2016 Big Ten Men's Lacrosse Tournament''' was held May 5 to May 7 at [[Homewood Field]] in  [[Baltimore, Maryland]]. The winner of the tournament received the [[Big Ten Conference]]'s [[automatic bid]] to the [[2016 NCAA Division I Men's Lacrosse Championship]]. Four teams from the [[Big Ten]] conference competed in the single elimination event.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lee|first1=Edward|title=Blue Jays, Terps view Big Ten men's lacrosse tourney differently|url=http://www.baltimoresun.com/sports/college/lacrosse/bs-sp-big-ten-tournament-advance-0505-20160504-story.html|work=Baltimore Sun|date=May 4, 2016}}</ref> The seeds were based upon the teams' regular season conference record with Penn State winning the head-to-head tie breaker over Ohio State to earn the #4 seed and final spot in the field.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bigten.org/sports/m-lacros/spec-rel/043016aad.html |title=Big Ten Announces Men\u2019s Lacrosse Tournament Bracket |date=April 30, 2016 |publisher=Big Ten Conference |access-date=May 1, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160506071133/http://www.bigten.org/sports/m-lacros/spec-rel/043016aad.html |archive-date=May 6, 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref> In the final, Maryland beat Rutgers 14-8.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Mills|first1=Kate|title=Men's Lacrosse: Terps win first Big Ten championship|url=http://www.abc2news.com/sports/college-sports/terps/terps-win-first-big-ten-championship|work=WMAR Baltimore|date=May 7, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Maryland downs Rutgers to win Big Ten men's lacrosse tourney|url=http://btn.com/2016/05/07/maryland-downs-rutgers-to-win-big-ten-mens-lacrosse-tourney-title/|work=Big Ten Network}}</ref>\n\n==Standings==\nOnly the top four teams in the Big Ten Conference advanced to the Big Ten Conference Tournament.<ref>{{Cite web |url = http://www.bigten.org/sports/m-lacros/spec-rel/050416aaa.html |title = Big Ten Men's Lacrosse Tournament Release |date = May 4, 2016 |publisher = Big Ten Conference |access-date = October 25, 2017 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20171026002630/http://www.bigten.org/sports/m-lacros/spec-rel/050416aaa.html |archive-date = October 26, 2017 |url-status = dead }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.hopkinssports.com/sports/m-lacros/2016-big10-tournament.html |title = Big Ten Men's Lacrosse Tournament |publisher = Johns Hopkins University}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n!Seed\n!School\n!Conference\n!Overall\n|-\n|1\n|align=left|[[Maryland Terrapins men's lacrosse|Maryland]] \u2021\n| 5\u20130 ||17\u20133\n|-\n|2\n|align=left|[[Rutgers Scarlet Knights men's lacrosse|Rutgers]] \n|3\u20132  ||11\u20135\n|-\n|3\n|align=left|[[Johns Hopkins Blue Jays men's lacrosse|Johns Hopkins]] \n|3\u20132  ||8\u20137 \n|-\n|4\n|align=left|[[Penn State Nittany Lions men's lacrosse|Penn State]] \n|2\u20133  ||8\u20137\n|-\n|DNQ\n|align=left|[[Ohio State Buckeyes men's lacrosse|Ohio State]]\n|2\u20133  ||7\u20138\n|- \n|DNQ\n|align=left|[[Michigan Wolverines men's lacrosse|Michigan]]\n|0\u20135  ||3\u201310\n|-\n| colspan=4 align=left|<small>\u2021 Big Ten regular season champions\n|}\n\n==Schedule==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 95%\"\n!Session\n!Game\n!Time\n!Matchup\n!Score\n!Television\n|-\n!colspan=6| Semifinals \u2013 Thursday, May 5\n|-\n|rowspan=2 align=center|1\n|align=center|1 \n|align=right|5:30 pm\n|align=center|#1 '''Maryland''' vs. #4 Penn State\n|align=center| 16\u20139\n|rowspan=1 align=center|Big Ten Network\n|-\n|align=center|2\n|align=right|8:00 pm\n|align=center|#2 '''Rutgers''' vs. #3 Johns Hopkins\n|align=center|14\u201312\n|rowspan=1 align=center|Big Ten Network\n|-\n!colspan=6| Championship \u2013 Saturday, May 7\n|-\n|rowspan=1 align=center|2\n|align=center|3\n|align=right|6:00pm\n|align=center| #1 '''Maryland''' vs. #2 Rutgers\n|align=center| 14\u20138\n|rowspan=1 align=center|ESPN2\n|-\n|colspan=6| <small>Game times in [[Eastern Time Zone|EST]]</small>\n|}\n\n==Bracket==\n'''Homewood Field \u2013 Baltimore, Maryland'''\n{{4TeamBracket\n| RD1=Semifinals<br />May 5\n| RD2=Championship Game<br />May 7\n| score-width=25\n| team-width=130\n| RD1-seed1=1\n| RD1-team1='''Maryland'''\n| RD1-score1='''16'''\n| RD1-seed2=4\n| RD1-team2=Penn State\n| RD1-score2=9\n\n| RD1-seed3=2\n| RD1-team3='''Rutgers'''\n| RD1-score3='''14'''\n| RD1-seed4=3\n| RD1-team4=Johns Hopkins\n| RD1-score4=12\n\n| RD2-seed1=1\n| RD2-team1='''Maryland'''\n| RD2-score1='''14'''\n| RD2-seed2=2\n| RD2-team2=Rutgers\n| RD2-score2=8\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2016 NCAA Division I men's lacrosse season|Big Ten Tournament]]\n[[Category:2016 in sports in Maryland|Big Ten Conference Men's Lacrosse]]\n[[Category:Big Ten Men's Lacrosse Tournament]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox tournament\n| name = [[Big Ten Conference Men's Lacrosse Tournament|Big Ten Conference<br/>Men's Lacrosse Tournament]]\n| sport = [[College lacrosse#NCAA Men's Lacrosse|College lacrosse]]\n| year = 2016\n| image =\n| caption = \n| location = Baltimore, Maryland\n| established = 2015\n| administrator =\n| tournament_format = Single elimination\n| host = Johns Hopkins University\n| venues = Homewood Field \n| teams = 4\n| champion = [[Maryland Terrapins men's lacrosse|Maryland]]\n| runner-up1 = [[Rutgers Scarlet Knights men's lacrosse|Rutgers]]\n| attendance = \n| mvp = \n| top_scorer = \n| top_try_scorer = \n| website = [http://www.hopkinssports.com/sports/m-lacros/2016-big10-tournament.html HopkinsSports.com]\n| previous = [[2015 Big Ten Conference Men's Lacrosse Tournament|2015]]\n| next = [[2017 Big Ten Conference Men's Lacrosse Tournament|2017]]\n}}\nThe '''2016 Big Ten Men's Lacrosse Tournament''' was held May 5 to May 7 at [[Homewood Field]] in  [[Baltimore, Maryland]]. The winner of the tournament received the [[Big Ten Conference]]'s [[automatic bid]] to the [[2016 NCAA Division I Men's Lacrosse Championship]]. Four teams from the [[Big Ten]] conference competed in the single elimination event.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lee|first1=Edward|title=Blue Jays, Terps view Big Ten men's lacrosse tourney differently|url=http://www.baltimoresun.com/sports/college/lacrosse/bs-sp-big-ten-tournament-advance-0505-20160504-story.html|work=Baltimore Sun|date=May 4, 2016}}</ref> The seeds were based upon the teams regular season conference record with Penn State winning the head-to-head tie breaker over Ohio State to earn the #4 seed and final spot in the field.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bigten.org/sports/m-lacros/spec-rel/043016aad.html |title=Big Ten Announces Men\u2019s Lacrosse Tournament Bracket |date=April 30, 2016 |publisher=Big Ten Conference |access-date=May 1, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160506071133/http://www.bigten.org/sports/m-lacros/spec-rel/043016aad.html |archive-date=May 6, 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref> In the final, Maryland beat Rutgers 14-8.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Mills|first1=Kate|title=Men's Lacrosse: Terps win first Big Ten championship|url=http://www.abc2news.com/sports/college-sports/terps/terps-win-first-big-ten-championship|work=WMAR Baltimore|date=May 7, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Maryland downs Rutgers to win Big Ten men's lacrosse tourney|url=http://btn.com/2016/05/07/maryland-downs-rutgers-to-win-big-ten-mens-lacrosse-tourney-title/|work=Big Ten Network}}</ref>\n\n==Standings==\nOnly the top four teams in the Big Ten Conference advanced to the Big Ten Conference Tournament.<ref>{{Cite web |url = http://www.bigten.org/sports/m-lacros/spec-rel/050416aaa.html |title = Big Ten Men's Lacrosse Tournament Release |date = May 4, 2016 |publisher = Big Ten Conference |access-date = October 25, 2017 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20171026002630/http://www.bigten.org/sports/m-lacros/spec-rel/050416aaa.html |archive-date = October 26, 2017 |url-status = dead }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.hopkinssports.com/sports/m-lacros/2016-big10-tournament.html |title = Big Ten Men's Lacrosse Tournament |publisher = Johns Hopkins University}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n!Seed\n!School\n!Conference\n!Overall\n|-\n|1\n|align=left|[[Maryland Terrapins men's lacrosse|Maryland]] \u2021\n| 5\u20130 ||17\u20133\n|-\n|2\n|align=left|[[Rutgers Scarlet Knights men's lacrosse|Rutgers]] \n|3\u20132  ||11\u20135\n|-\n|3\n|align=left|[[Johns Hopkins Blue Jays men's lacrosse|Johns Hopkins]] \n|3\u20132  ||8\u20137 \n|-\n|4\n|align=left|[[Penn State Nittany Lions men's lacrosse|Penn State]] \n|2\u20133  ||8\u20137\n|-\n|DNQ\n|align=left|[[Ohio State Buckeyes men's lacrosse|Ohio State]]\n|2\u20133  ||7\u20138\n|- \n|DNQ\n|align=left|[[Michigan Wolverines men's lacrosse|Michigan]]\n|0\u20135  ||3\u201310\n|-\n| colspan=4 align=left|<small>\u2021 Big Ten regular season champions\n|}\n\n==Schedule==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 95%\"\n!Session\n!Game\n!Time\n!Matchup\n!Score\n!Television\n|-\n!colspan=6| Semifinals \u2013 Thursday, May 5\n|-\n|rowspan=2 align=center|1\n|align=center|1 \n|align=right|5:30 pm\n|align